1012
01:13:52,891 --> 01:13:55,086
"Burn the British," that's diner talk.

1013
01:13:57,096 --> 01:13:58,893
Friday's a tough one.

1014
01:13:59,431 --> 01:14:01,365
Saturday's the hardest, I think.

1015
01:14:01,467 --> 01:14:04,368
Looks like
you're doing pretty good, though.

1016
01:14:04,703 --> 01:14:06,261
You stuck on any?

1017
01:14:09,775 --> 01:14:11,140
Give me one.

1018
01:14:12,177 --> 01:14:15,704
Sometimes you get one,
the rest of them fall into place.

1019
01:14:16,281 --> 01:14:18,875
What makes you think I need your help?

1020
01:14:18,984 --> 01:14:20,884
It's a tough puzzle.

1021
01:14:22,421 --> 01:14:25,481
Come on. Six, down. I'm pretty good at it.

1022
01:14:27,826 --> 01:14:29,726
What's the matter, man?

1023
01:14:31,196 --> 01:14:33,027
I'm just trying to talk here.

1024
01:14:33,132 --> 01:14:35,862
- You want coffee?
- I don't want nothing from you.

1025
01:14:35,968 --> 01:14:37,333
All right?

1026
01:14:37,569 --> 01:14:40,094
- Thank you.
- What's up, Samel?

1027
01:14:40,539 --> 01:14:42,336
What you doing here?

1028
01:14:42,441 --> 01:14:44,136
Had to get out the house, man.

1029
01:14:44,243 --> 01:14:47,610
Trying to find a little peace and quiet.
You know what I'm saying?

1030
01:14:48,514 --> 01:14:49,981
Same with me.

1031
01:14:50,082 --> 01:14:52,346
Getting out of the house, I mean.

1032
01:14:52,451 --> 01:14:53,941
Samel, is it?

1033
01:14:54,720 --> 01:14:56,347
My name is John.

1034
01:14:57,356 --> 01:15:00,120
What are you doing? What do you want?

1035
01:15:00,392 --> 01:15:02,952
I'm just trying to make conversation.

1036
01:15:03,295 --> 01:15:05,263
It's an old-fashioned pastime.

1037
01:15:05,364 --> 01:15:06,763
You in school?

1038
01:15:11,370 --> 01:15:13,964
I'm about to go to Howard University.

1039
01:15:14,072 --> 01:15:15,664
Very impressive.

1040
01:15:16,375 --> 01:15:19,071
- What?
- I didn't say Harvard, I said Howard.

1041
01:15:19,178 --> 01:15:23,547
I heard you. Howard University,
Washington D.C. It's a very good school.

1042
01:15:26,018 --> 01:15:27,212
Come on.

1043
01:15:27,319 --> 01:15:30,345
There's got to be
some sports questions in there.

1044
01:15:30,456 --> 01:15:31,855
My wife, she would always ask me...

1045
01:15:31,957 --> 01:15:36,485
Why don't you go home to your wife and
do your own crossword puzzle with her?

1046
01:15:36,595 --> 01:15:38,085
I wish I could.

1047
01:15:38,897 --> 01:15:40,956
I buried her two weeks ago.

1048
01:15:41,633 --> 01:15:43,760
That's why I'm out wandering around...

1049
01:15:43,869 --> 01:15:46,201
I'm trying to get it off my mind.

1050
01:15:48,106 --> 01:15:49,937
Come on. Twelve, down.

1051
01:15:50,609 --> 01:15:51,906
Try me out.

1052
01:15:56,982 --> 01:15:59,678
Snowfall. Nine letters, starts with "A."

1053
01:16:03,322 --> 01:16:06,348
- Sorry to hear about your wife.
- Thank you.

1054
01:16:15,400 --> 01:16:16,867
I don't know.

1055
01:16:17,636 --> 01:16:19,228
Okay, you got me.

1056
01:16:25,844 --> 01:16:28,335
I'm staying with my sons for now...

1057
01:16:28,914 --> 01:16:30,677
see what they need.

1058
01:16:31,783 --> 01:16:33,011
Good man.

1059
01:16:33,986 --> 01:16:35,613
Nice you're in their life.

1060
01:16:35,721 --> 01:16:38,849
- Pardon me?
- I said it's nice you're in their life.

1061
01:16:40,559 --> 01:16:42,186
My father's dead.

1062
01:16:43,161 --> 01:16:44,958
Sorry to hear that.

1063
01:16:46,064 --> 01:16:47,861
- That's hard.
- Right.

1064
01:16:50,335 --> 01:16:52,394
I could've been a better father.

1065
01:16:53,639 --> 01:16:56,369
I wasn't there for the important times.

1066
01:16:56,475 --> 01:16:58,204
The teenage years.

1067
01:16:58,310 --> 01:17:01,336
When I finally figured things out
and came home...

1068
01:17:03,348 --> 01:17:05,282
she was already sick...

1069
01:17:05,784 --> 01:17:07,775
and I realized how much I missed.

1070
01:17:07,886 --> 01:17:09,251
So you fucked up.

1071
01:17:09,354 --> 01:17:12,016
I had to leave. We were fighting all the time.

1072
01:17:12,124 --> 01:17:14,217
I thought it would be worse if I stayed.

1073
01:17:14,326 --> 01:17:15,884
How could it be?

1074
01:17:15,994 --> 01:17:19,054
You get in a beef with a woman
and it makes you leave your kids?

1075
01:17:19,932 --> 01:17:22,833
That's weak, man.

1076
01:17:24,436 --> 01:17:25,960
I mean, look...

1077
01:17:26,538 --> 01:17:29,166
your wife is dead now
and you're sobbing about her.

1078
01:17:29,274 --> 01:17:30,673
I feel that.

1079
01:17:31,176 --> 01:17:32,438
That's real.

1080
01:17:33,011 --> 01:17:36,378
When she was alive,
your kids were sobbing about you.

1081
01:17:38,750 --> 01:17:40,217
Good point.

1082
01:17:45,824 --> 01:17:47,121
Avalanche.

1083
01:17:48,093 --> 01:17:49,355
- What?
- Avalanche.

1084
01:17:49,461 --> 01:17:51,588
Nine letters for a snowfall.

1085
01:17:54,600 --> 01:17:55,692
See?

1086
01:18:00,305 --> 01:18:02,239
I was bullshitting you.

1087
01:18:02,774 --> 01:18:04,867
What, you're not really going to Howard?

1088
01:18:04,977 --> 01:18:07,411
No, hell, yeah, I'm going to Howard.

1089
01:18:07,512 --> 01:18:09,207
I meant about my father.

1090
01:18:09,314 --> 01:18:10,838
He ain't dead.

1091
01:18:11,483 --> 01:18:13,713
May as well have been
the last 15 years, though...

1092
01:18:13,819 --> 01:18:15,844
he damn sure wasn't around being my dad.

1093
01:18:17,756 --> 01:18:20,156
You haven't seen him in 15 years?

1094
01:18:20,392 --> 01:18:22,360
I'm supposed to call him.

1095
01:18:23,261 --> 01:18:25,456
I don't have to, legally.

1096
01:18:27,866 --> 01:18:31,063
But my foster mom wants to adopt me.
She wants me to call him.

1097
01:18:31,169 --> 01:18:32,466
All right.

1098
01:18:32,804 --> 01:18:35,500
- What are you gonna say to him?
- Nothing.

1099
01:18:36,975 --> 01:18:38,636
I ain't calling.

1100
01:18:38,977 --> 01:18:41,207
How do you know what happened?

1101
01:18:41,346 --> 01:18:43,314
Do you know his story?

1102
01:18:43,415 --> 01:18:45,975
- Because you never know.
- I don't care about his story.

1103
01:18:46,084 --> 01:18:47,642
I care about mine.

1104
01:18:48,520 --> 01:18:51,785
And if I ever have kids,
I'm gonna be a better father than he was.

1105
01:18:51,890 --> 01:18:54,120
I will never leave my family.

1106
01:18:55,360 --> 01:18:58,022
We all wanna be better than our fathers.

1107
01:19:29,995 --> 01:19:32,463
"I was floating above it all

1108
